# Note Management

Single source of truth for everything {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} tells the agent to remember — forward-looking notes ("for tomorrow") AND standing rules ("stop flagging Linear emails"). All entries live in `state/directives.json`. No parallel store, no drift.

## Two surfaces, one store

| Surface | Trigger | Action written |
|---|---|---|
| **Forward note** | "note this", "for tomorrow", "don't forget", "remind me", "add to standup" | `remind` with `until=<date>` |
| **Standing rule** | "stop flagging X", "always archive Y", "X is done", "snooze X until Z" | `suppress` / `snooze` / `archive` |

Both go through the same CLI. Both live in the same JSON array.

## The directives store

**Path**: `state/directives.json` (workspace root). Flat array of objects.

```json
[
  {
    "id": "stable-slug",
    "action": "suppress" | "snooze" | "archive" | "remind",
    "match": ["alias 1", "alias 2"],
    "scope": ["morning-brief", "email-processing", "*"],
    "until": "YYYY-MM-DD",
    "note": "{{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} context YYYY-MM-DD"
  }
]
```

| Field | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `id` | stable slug, used for update/delete |
| `action` | `suppress` (never surface), `snooze` (suppress until date), `archive` (auto-archive email/notification matching), `remind` (surface on date — forward notes) |
| `match` | list of strings to fuzzy-match against item text (title, subject, sender, channel — all string values of the item joined) |
| `scope` | list of skills this applies to; `["*"]` = all |
| `until` | ISO date, required for `snooze` and `remind`, null otherwise |
| `note` | source + reason, free-text |

## Forward note flow

Any message where {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} is handing off something to be remembered for a future Daily Brief or standup — even casual phrasings. Err on the side of capturing.

**Trigger phrases (not exhaustive):**
"note this" · "note that X" · "for tomorrow" · "for tomorrow standup" · "add to my daily brief" · "add to standup" · "mention this tomorrow" · "don't forget X" · "remind me about X" · "carry this forward" · "put this in tomorrow's brief" · "tell me in the morning" · "surface this tomorrow"

**Not in scope:**
- Task creation ("add a todo", "add to my shit list") → `task-manager`
- Wiki / institutional knowledge ("document this", "save to wiki") → `superposition-wiki`
- Profile updates ("remember this about me") → `profile-updater`

If ambiguous, capture here and route later.

**Mechanism** — same turn, no waiting. Single CLI call:

```bash
cd {{WORKSPACE_ROOT}} && python3 skills/note-management/scripts/directives.py add \
  --action remind \
  --until <YYYY-MM-DD> \
  --match "<note text>" \
  --scope morning-brief \
  --note "captured $(date +%F)"
```

Pick `--until` based on {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}}'s phrasing:
- "for tomorrow" / "tomorrow standup" / default → tomorrow's date
- "for today" / "today's brief" → today's date
- Explicit date → that date

Confirm with one line in chat. That's the whole capture flow.

**Optional — patch already-rendered artifacts.** If the note is for TODAY and today's brief file (`archive/daily_schedules/daily_schedule_<today>.md`) already exists, append the note under a `## Notes from {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}}` section. Same for the target standup file (`archive/standup_notes/standup_notes_<date>.md`) if present. Skip if the files don't exist — morning-brief will read the directive on next run.

## Standing rule flow

When {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} says "stop flagging X" / "always archive Y" / "X is done" / "snooze X until Z":
```bash
python3 skills/note-management/scripts/directives.py add \
  --action suppress \
  --match "<alias>" --match "<another alias>" \
  --scope morning-brief \
  --note "<{{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} context — source date>"
```

For snooze: `--action snooze --until YYYY-MM-DD`.
For archive: `--action archive` (email/notification sender-or-subject patterns; scope typically `email-processing`).

Full CLI:
```
directives.py list [--scope X] [--action Y]
directives.py check "<text>" [--scope X]
directives.py add --action A --match "..." [--match ...] [--scope S] [--until DATE] --note "..."
directives.py remove <id>
directives.py expire            # drop past-date snoozes + remind
directives.py reminders [--scope X]   # today's active remind directives
```

## For consumers (morning-brief, email-processing, slack-triage, heartbeat, ...)

Before flagging any item, call:
```bash
python3 skills/note-management/scripts/directives.py check "<item text>" --scope <your-skill>
```

If `surface: false` → drop the item. Respect the action in the result.

To fetch today's forward notes:
```bash
python3 skills/note-management/scripts/directives.py reminders --scope <your-skill>
```

Or from Python:
```python
import sys
sys.path.insert(0, "skills/note-management/scripts")
from directives import should_surface, reminders
```

## Matching

Fuzzy: normalize (lowercase, strip non-alnum) + substring + token-set-ratio (threshold 0.6).

Match strings can be UUIDs (exact), domains (substring), or phrases (fuzzy). Include whatever you want matched.

## Lifecycle

| Action | Auto-cleanup |
|---|---|
| `suppress` | Never — remove explicitly with `directives.py remove <id>` |
| `snooze` | `expire` drops when `until <= today` (item resurfaces naturally if still open) |
| `archive` | Never — remove explicitly |
| `remind` | `expire` drops when `until < today` (one-shot delivery on the `until` date) |

Nightly hygiene (default ~23:00 {{USER_TIMEZONE}}) runs `directives.py expire`.

## Rules

- **Never rely on chat memory alone.** Every note + rule writes to disk, same turn.
- **Don't batch.** Each note captured as it is said.
- **Don't editorialize.** Capture {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}}'s words; don't summarize or polish.
- **Surface capture failures.** If the helper errors, tell {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} immediately.
- **Never hand-edit `state/directives.json`.** Use the CLI.

## Hard rule reference

This skill implements both the "Direct Note Capture" rule and the "Directives — unified surfacing rules" rule from `MEMORY.md`. If those files disagree, `MEMORY.md` wins.

## Design note

One skill owns every "X told the agent to remember/forget Y" surface: capture, query, expire. No companion skills. Consumers call `directives.py` directly.
